*
         * @prop {String} propertyName
         * @description
         *   The name of the property to be used in requests and events.

*
         * @prop {Boolean} active
         * @description
         *   Determines if this property is active and should be displayed.

*
         * @prop {Boolean} isEditable
         * @description
         *   Determines if the value of this property can be changed using a form.

*
         * @prop {Boolean} isExpandable
         * @description
         *   Determines if the property card can be expanded or not.

*
         * @prop {Boolean|undefined} isExpanded
         * @description
         *   Whether the property card is expanded by default or not.

*
         * @prop {String} label
         * @description
         *   The label of the property card.

*
         * @prop {String} formSchemaUrl
         * @description
         *   The URL of the endpoint to fetch the form schema from.

*
         * @prop {String} propertyUpdateUrl
         * @description
         *   The URL of the endpoint to update the property values.

*
         * @prop {Object|undefined} formRequestParams
         * @description
         *   Parameters to include in the form schema request.

*
         * @prop {Boolean} formMode
         * @default false
         * @description
         *     Indicates if the edit form is active.

*
         * @prop {String} columnLayout
         * @description
         *   The current column layout.

*
         * @prop {Function|undefined} customColumnLayoutCols
         * @description
         *   Custom handler that returns the number of columns
         *      that the component should use.

*
         * @prop {Boolean} showCloseButton
         * @description
         *   Whether to show the close button or not.

because the push event can be faster as the request "execution".
